xxl.core.relational.query.predicates
Class Predicates

java.lang.Object
  xxl.core.relational.query.predicates.Predicates

public class Predicates
extends Object

This class provides static methods for creating ready to use instances of a predicate node in a directed acyclic graph. Beside these methods, it contains constants for identifying local metadata fragments inside a predicate node's global metadata, methods for accessing them and local metadata factories for updating them.

Method Detail

newPredicate

public static final Node newPredicate(String type,
                                      int numberOfChildren,
                                      int numberOfParents)
Creates a new predicate node providing the given local metadata fragments and registers factory methods for this metadata fragments.

Parameters:
type - a string identifying the type of the predicate node to be returned.
numberOfChildren - the number of children required by the returned predicate node. It can be set to Nodes.VARIABLE for indicating that the predicate node does not need a fixed number of subpredicates.
numberOfParents - the number of parents required by the returned predicate node. It can be set to Nodes.VARIABLE for indicating that the predicate node does not need a fixed number of parental predicates.
Returns:
a new predicate node providing the given local metadata fragments.

Returns:
the type of the given predicate node.
